result.execSummary:
The defendant Devin Bernard Seiler was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • False Imprisonment [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.30.
  • Battery [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Battery [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Devin Bernard Seiler in court with attorney Joel Kenneth Larimore.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Agreement reached.  Defendant will enter into DAGPA on count 1 on the soon to be filed Information with a 2 yr. agreement with addt'l terms; will plead guilty to counts 2 & 3 with 2 yrs. probation, no contact provision and argue jail; counts 4 & 5 will be dismissed.  On the other matter before the court the motion to revoke pre-existing DAGPA, defendant will agree he violated the agreement, place on 1 yr. probation with condition 5 days jail consecutive the battery charges.  Court inquires why not 2 yrs. probation on that case.  Counsel agree to 2 yrs.  Atty Larimore also requests expungement.  Court informs he can't expunge dismissed charges and case with charges of conviction and dismissed charges.    State confirms complied with victim notification requirements and informs he has not received any communication from them.  Defendant waives his right to PH in 16CF42.  State files copy of Information with the court, defense counsel confirms receipt.  Court advises defendant of charges/max. penalties, constitutional rights and felony prohibitions if convicted of felony.  Court summarizes the agreement with defendant.  Subject to negotiations, court revokes DPA in 15CM60, accepts defendant plea and finds him guilty.  Subject to the DPA in count 1, defendants pleads guilty; defendant pleads no contest to counts 2 & 3.  PLQ/WOR form filed with the court and reviewed with defendant. Court finds defendant's waiver of his constitutional rights and pleas done knowingly & voluntarily, accepts pleas and finds defendant guilty of counts 2 & 3, DRI counts 3 & 4 for restitution purposes and agreed by counsel.  Court approves DPA in count 1.  State's closing arguments and requests 2 yrs probation, 20 days jail on misdemeanor battery, 5 days on possession, no jail credit.  Defense closing argument, requests 5 days jail on drug charge and probation and straight probation on battery charges, don't think the extra 20 days are necessary.  Agree no sentence credit.  Court has few questions for defense counsel/defendant.  Court adds a condition to demonstrate responsibility by diligently seeking or maintaining F/T employment.  Under the present law I can't expunge.  When you get off probation, check with court or probation to see if the law has changed.  Your cases has mixes of convictions and dismissals and I can't expunge 1/2 of a file.  At the present time I won't approve expungement.  If law changes, the only way I would consider it is if you have no violations of probation.  In 15CM60 withhold sentence and place on 2 yrs. probation with conditions:  serve 5 days in the PCJ; provide DNA sample; pay costs believe $443; comply with any assessment or counseling set up by P&P.  In counts 2 & 3 in 16CF42, withhold sentence place on 2 yrs. probation concurrent to eachother; provide DNA sample; pay costs on count 2, waive costs on count 3; no contact with named individuals to be provided to clerk by DA; DA indicated you intimidated a witness which he didn't charge and if its true you actively participated and threatened harm to someone else so adopt recommendation and sentence you do 20 days PCJ consecutive to the 5 days w/ work release, report 5/10 at 4:00 p.m.; set up work release ahead of time; addt'l cond:  comply with any assesssment or counseling set up by P&P; demonstrate responsibility by seeking & maintaining F/T employment.  Advised of appeal rights.
Adjourned initial appearance on May 1, 2017 at 10:00 am.
